
[1]substratum

   SUBSTRA'TUM, n. [L. substratus, spread under; sub and sterno.]

   1. That which is laid or spread under; a layer of earth lying under
   another. In agriculture, the subsoil.

   2. In metaphysics, the matter or substance supposed to furnish the
   basis in which the perceptible qualities inhere.
